0
\begin{pmatrix}A & 0 \\ B & C\end{pmatrix}
\det \begin{pmatrix}A & 0 \\ B & C\end{pmatrix} = \det (A) \det (C)
-i
\det M = \det \begin{pmatrix}2 I_n & 0 \\ iI_n & I_n \end{pmatrix} = \det(2I_n) \det(I_n) = 2^n
